    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ceb09b94_38851f84",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/main-kernel-parameters.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 209,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-18T21:12:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the file is deleted, what is the worst case scenario? What if the file doesn\u0027t already exist when the AVD is booted for the first time? We would need to re-examine how we construct kernel parameters for every case. If we end up adding more kernel parameters to the kernel parameters file, it will be very difficult to track down breakages cause by incompatible kernel parameters files with different emulator versions.\n\nSo, can we make this specific to verified boot only? I.e., create a file just for the verified boot parameters, and read from the file outside of main-kernel-parmeters.cpp, and pass the verified boot parameters to |emulator_getKernelParameters| as an extra parameters. That way, it\u0027s much more obvious what\u0027s going on just from reading the code, and crash reports in this function will be a lot clearer as well as to what part of kernel parameters parsing failed.\n\nI recommend instead, creating a new class in android/android-emu/android/emulation just for parsing verified boot parameters into kernel parameters, and to have a specific case here for adding to |params| when there are kernel parameters for verified boot.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 206,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 209,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "027f7160abd9644996cc7275912f2666951784ee",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "76e9bd51_30c0fd47",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/main-kernel-parameters.cpp",
